---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout
        title="Terms of Service | AppsByLuke"
        description="These Terms of Service constitute a legally binding agreement between AppsByLuke and you, governing the use of my Services and Website."
>
    <div class="bg-blue-200 py-8 md:py-16 overflow-y-auto border-y-4 border-black">
        <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 md:px-6 lg:px-8">
            <div class="bg-white border-4 border-black p-4 md:p-8 shadow-[8px_8px_0px_0px_rgba(0,0,0,1)] relative">
                <div class="absolute top-0 right-0 w-16 h-16 md:w-24 md:h-24 bg-yellow-400 border-4 border-black transform rotate-12 translate-x-4 -translate-y-4 md:translate-x-8 md:-translate-y-8 z-0"></div>
                <div class="absolute bottom-0 left-0 w-12 h-12 md:w-20 md:h-20 bg-pink-400 border-4 border-black rounded-full -translate-x-6 translate-y-6 md:-translate-x-10 md:translate-y-10 z-0"></div>

                <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl lg:text-5xl font-bold text-black mb-8 transform -rotate-1 break-words relative z-10 pr-20 md:pr-0">
                    Terms of Service
                </h1>

                <div class="mb-4">
                    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">1. Introduction</h2>
                    <p>These Terms of Service ("Terms") constitute a legally binding agreement between Łukasz Ziaja
                        ("Company," "I," "me," or "my"), operating under the business name AppsByLuke, and you
                        ("Client," "you," or "your") governing the use of my Services and Website.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="mb-4">
                    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">2. Definitions</h2>
                    <div class="ml-4 space-y-4">
                        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-2">2.1. Company</h3>
                        <p>"Company" refers to Łukasz Ziaja, a sole proprietorship registered at al. Wiśniowa 36a/304
                            53-137 Wrocław, Poland, operating under the business name AppsByLuke.</p>

                        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-2">2.2. Services</h3>
                        <p>The Company provides two primary service categories:</p>
                        <ul class="list-disc list-inside ml-4 space-y-4">
                            <li>Developer as Subscription</li>
                            <li>App Packages</li>
                        </ul>

                        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-2">2.3. Technical Stack</h3>
                        <p>The Company utilizes the following technologies for service delivery:</p>
                        <ul class="list-disc list-inside ml-4 space-y-4">
                            <li>Languages: JavaScript, TypeScript, PHP</li>
                            <li>Frameworks & Libraries: Symfony, Laravel, Vue.js, Astro, NestJS, Nuxt</li>
                            <li>Runtime Environments: Node.js</li>
                            <li>Databases & Messaging: MySQL, PostgreSQL, MongoDB, Redis, Elasticsearch, Apache Kafka,
                                RabbitMQ
                            </li>
                            <li>Frontend & Design: Bootstrap, Tailwind CSS</li>
                            <li>CMS & E-commerce: Pimcore, WordPress, WooCommerce</li>
                            <li>DevOps & Infrastructure: Docker, Kubernetes, Terraform, AWS, GCP, On-Premise
                                Infrastructure, Git, GitHub Actions, Cloudflare
                            </li>
                            <li>Monitoring & Analytics: Grafana, Uptime Kuma, Prometheus, Sentry, Google Analytics,
                                Google Search Console, Kibana
                            </li>
                            <li>AI: OpenAI, Claude, MindsDB</li>
                            <li>Testing & Code Quality: Cypress, Selenium, PHPUnit, Jest, PhpSpec, PhpStan, ESLint,
                                Prettier, Rector
                            </li>
                        </ul>

                        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-2">2.4. Website</h3>
                        <p>"Website" refers to the Company's website, accessible at https://appsbyluke.com</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="mb-4">
                    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">3. Service Terms</h2>
                    <div class="ml-4 space-y-4">
                        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-2">3.1. Developer as Subscription</h3>
                        <div class="ml-4 space-y-4">
                            <h4 class="text-lg font-bold mb-2">a) Subscription Plans and Capacity</h4>
                            <ul class="list-disc list-inside ml-4 space-y-4">
                                <li>Standard Tier: One (1) concurrent development task</li>
                                <li>Pro Tier: Two (2) concurrent development tasks</li>
                                <li>Unlimited development requests can be submitted</li>
                                <li>Tasks are processed according to the concurrent task limit</li>
                            </ul>

                            <h4 class="text-lg font-bold mb-2">b) Task States and Workflow</h4>
                            <p>Tasks progress through the following states:</p>
                            <ul class="list-decimal list-inside ml-4 space-y-4">
                                <li>"Requested" - Initial task submission by Client</li>
                                <li>"Approved" - Task approved for development</li>
                                <li>"In Progress" - Active development phase</li>
                                <li>"Delivered" - Development completed and ready for review</li>
                                <li>"Accepted" or "Changes Requested" - Client review outcome</li>
                                <li>"Canceled" - Optional state if Client chooses to terminate the task</li>
                            </ul>

                            <h4 class="text-lg font-bold mb-2">c) Service Delivery</h4>
                            <ul class="list-disc list-inside ml-4 space-y-4">
                                <li>Development services provided during business hours (Monday-Friday, CET timezone)
                                </li>
                                <li>Code delivery through private GitHub repositories</li>
                                <li>Documentation provided with each delivery</li>
                                <li>Updates provided through requests management panel</li>
                                <li>Slack updates available upon request</li>
                            </ul>

                            <h4 class="text-lg font-bold mb-2">d) Communication Policy</h4>
                            <ul class="list-disc list-inside ml-4 space-y-4">
                                <li>Primary communication through requests management panel</li>
                                <li>Meetings available on fair-usage basis, prioritizing efficient communication and
                                    development time
                                </li>
                                <li>Additional communication channels (e.g., Slack) as agreed upon</li>
                            </ul>

                            <h4 class="text-lg font-bold mb-2">e) Quality Assurance</h4>
                            <ul class="list-disc list-inside ml-4 space-y-4">
                                <li>Code review and testing performed before delivery</li>
                                <li>Implementation of automated tests where applicable</li>
                                <li>Security best practices implementation</li>
                                <li>Performance optimization as standard practice</li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>

                        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-2">3.2. App Packages</h3>
                        <div class="ml-4 space-y-4">
                            <h4 class="text-lg font-bold mb-2">a) Package Types and Timelines</h4>
                            <ul class="list-disc list-inside ml-4 space-y-4">
                                <li>MVP Launchpad: 4-6 weeks delivery timeframe</li>
                                <li>Scale-up Accelerator: 8-10 weeks delivery timeframe</li>
                                <li>Enterprise Powerhouse: 12-16 weeks delivery timeframe</li>
                            </ul>
                            <p>Note: Actual delivery times may vary based on project complexity and requirements</p>

                            <h4 class="text-lg font-bold mb-2">b) Development Process</h4>
                            <p>Each package includes:</p>
                            <ul class="list-disc list-inside ml-4 space-y-4">
                                <li>Custom designed responsive web application</li>
                                <li>Core feature implementation based on package level</li>
                                <li>Documentation and codebase delivery</li>
                                <li>Development using the Primary Technology Stack (Section 2.3.a)</li>
                            </ul>

                            <h4 class="text-lg font-bold mb-2">c) Project Scope</h4>
                            <ul class="list-disc list-inside ml-4 space-y-4">
                                <li>Scope defined and agreed upon before development begins</li>
                                <li>Features and functionalities specified by package level</li>
                                <li>Additional features can be discussed as extensions</li>
                                <li>Architecture planning appropriate to project scale</li>
                            </ul>

                            <h4 class="text-lg font-bold mb-2">d) Delivery and Implementation</h4>
                            <ul class="list-disc list-inside ml-4 space-y-4">
